death. }3.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Now then  take thy weapons, both thy quiver and thy bow, and go into the plain, and get me venison,  }4.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  and make me meats, as I like them, and  bring them to me that I may eat, that my soul may bless thee, before I die. }5.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And Rebecca heard Isaac
 speaking to Esau his son; and  Esau went to the plain to procure venison for his father. }6.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And Rebecca said to Jacob her younger son, Behold, I heard thy father  speaking to Esau thy brother, saying, }7.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Bring me venison, and prepare me meats, that I may 
eat and bless thee before the Lord before I  die. }8.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Now then my son, hearken to me, as I command thee. }9.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And go to the cattle and take for me thence two kids, tender and good,  and I will make them meats for thy father, as he likes. }10.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And thou shalt br
ing them in to thy father, and he shall eat, that thy father may  bless thee before he dies. }11.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And Jacob said to his mother Rebecca, Esau my brother is a hairy man, and I a smooth man. }12.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033   Peradventure my father may feel me, and I shall be before him as
 one ill intentioned, and I shall bring upon me a curse, and not a blessing.  }13.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And his mother said to him, On me be thy curse, son; only hearken to my voice, and go and bring them me. }14.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  So he went and took  and brought them to his mother; and his moth
er made meats, as his father liked them. }15.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And Rebecca having taken the fine raiment of  her elder son Esau which was with her in the house, put it on Jacob her  younger son. }16.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And she put on his arms the skins of the kids,  and on the bare parts of hi
s neck. }17.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And she gave the meats, and the loaves which she had prepared, into the hands of Jacob her son.  }18.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And he brought them to his father, and said, Father; and he said, Behold I am here; who art thou, son?. }19.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And Jacob said to his  father, I, E
sau thy first-born, have done as thou toldest me; rise, sit, and eat of my venison, that thy  soul may bless me. }20.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And Isaac said  to his son, What is this which thou hast quickly found? And he said, That which the Lord thy God presented before me. }21.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  A
nd Isaac  said to Jacob, Draw nigh to me, and I will feel thee, son, if thou art my son Esau or not. }22.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And Jacob drew nigh to his father Isaac, and  he felt him, and said, The voice is Jacob's voice, but the hands are the hands of Esau. }23.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And he knew h
im not, for his hands were as the  hands of his brother Esau, hairy; and he blessed him, }24.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  and he said, Art thou my son Esau? and he said, I am. }25.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And he said, Bring  hither, and I will eat of thy venison, son, that my soul may bless thee; and he broug
ht it near to him, and he ate, and he brought him wine,  and he drank. }26.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And Isaac his father said to him, Draw nigh to me, and kiss me, son. }27.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And he drew nigh and kissed him, and smelled  the smell of his garments, and blessed him, and said, Behold, 
the smell of my son is as the smell of an abundant field, which the Lord has  blessed. }28.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And may God give thee of the dew of heaven, and of the fatness of the earth and abundance of corn and wine. }29.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And let  nations serve thee, and princes bow down to 
thee, and be thou lord of thy brother, and the sons of thy father shall do thee reverence;  accursed is he that curses thee, and blessed is he that blesses thee. }30.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And it came to pass after Isaac had ceased blessing his son Jacob,  it even came to pass, 
just when Jacob had gone out from the presence of Isaac his father, that Esau his brother came in from his hunting.  }31.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And he also had made meats and brought them to his father; and he said to his father, Let my father arise and eat of his son's venison,
  that thy soul may bless me. }32.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And Isaac his father said to him, Who art thou? And he said, I am thy first-born son Esau. }33.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And Isaac  was amazed with very great amazement, and said, Who then is it that has procured venison for me and brought it to me
? and I have eaten  of all before thou camest, and I have blessed him, and he shall be blessed. }34.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And it came to pass when Esau heard the words of his  father Isaac, he cried out with a great and very bitter cry, and said, Bless, I pray thee, me also, fa
ther. }35.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And he said to him, Thy brother  has come with subtlety, and taken thy blessing. }36.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And he said, Rightly was his name called Jacob, for lo! this second time has he  supplanted me; he has both taken my birthright and now he has taken my blessing;
 and Esau said to his father, Hast thou not left a blessing  for me, father? }37.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And Isaac answered and said to Esau, If I have made him thy lord, and have made all his brethren his servants, and  have strengthened him with corn and wine, what then shall I
 do for thee, son? }38.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And Esau said to his father, Hast thou only one blessing  father? Bless, I pray thee, me also, father. And Isaac being troubled, Esau cried aloud and wept. }39.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And Isaac his father answered and  said to him, Behold, thy dwelling shal
l be of the fatness of the earth, and of the dew of heaven from above. }40.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And thou shalt live by thy  sword, and shalt serve thy brother; and there shall be a time when thou shalt break and loosen his yoke from off thy neck. }41.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And Esau  was angry with J
acob because of the blessing, with which his father blessed him; and Esau said in his mind, Let the days of my father's  mourning draw nigh, that I may slay my brother Jacob.   }}
