\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s8\cf0\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af3\afs20\lang1033\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe1033\hich\f3\fs20\lang1033\loch\f3\fs20\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f3\fs20\lang1033\i0\b0 16.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  He that keeps the commandments keeps his own soul; but he that despises his ways shall perish. }17.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  He that has pity on the poor  lends to the Lord; and he will recompense to him according to his gift. }18.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Chasten thy son, for so he shall be hopeful; an
d be not exalted  in thy soul to haughtiness. }19.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  A malicious man shall be severely punished, and if he commit injury, he shall also lose his life. }20.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Hear, son,  the instruction of thy father, that thou mayest be wise at thy latter end. }21.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  There are man
y thoughts in a man's heart; but the counsel of the  Lord abides for ever. }22.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Mercy is a fruit to a man: and a poor man is better than a rich liar. }23.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  The fear of the Lord is life to a man: and  he shall lodge without fear in places where knowledge is no
t seen. }24.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  He that unjustly hides his hands in his bosom, will not even bring  them up to his mouth. }25.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  When a pestilent character is scourged, a simple man is made wiser: and if thou reprove a wise man, he will  understand discretion.   }}
