\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s8\cf0\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af3\afs20\lang1033\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe1033\hich\f3\fs20\lang1033\loch\f3\fs20\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f3\fs20\lang1033\i0\b0 3.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  To do justly and to speak truth, are more pleasing to God than the blood of sacrifices. }4.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  A high minded man is stout-hearted in his  pride; and the lamp of the wicked is sin. }6.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  He that gathers treasures with a lying tongue pursues vanity on to the sna
res of death. }7.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033   Destruction shall lodge with the ungodly; for they refuse to do justly. }8.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  To the forward God sends forward ways; for his works are pure  and right. }9.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  It is better to dwell in a corner on the house-top, than in plastered rooms with unrig
hteousness, and in an open house. }10.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  The  soul of the ungodly shall not be pitied by any man. }11.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  When an intemperate man is punished the simple becomes wiser: and a wise man  understanding will receive knowledge. }12.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  A righteous man understands the heart
s of the ungodly: and despises the ungodly for their  wickedness. }13.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  He that stops his ears from hearing the poor, himself also shall cry, and there shall be none to hear him. }14.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  A secret gift  calms anger: but he that forbears to give stirs up strong wr
ath. }15.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  It is the joy of the righteous to do judgment: but a holy man is  abominable with evil-doers. }16.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  A man that wanders out of the way of righteousness, shall rest in the congregation of giants. }17.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  A poor  man loves mirth, loving wine and oil in abu
ndance; }18.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  and a transgressor is the abomination of a righteous man. }19.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  It is better to dwell in  a wilderness than with a quarrelsome and talkative and passionate woman. }20.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  A desirable treasure will rest on the mouth of the wise; but  foolish men will 
swallow it up. }21.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  The way of righteousness and mercy will find life and glory.   }}
