\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s8\cf0\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af3\afs20\lang1033\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe1033\hich\f3\fs20\lang1033\loch\f3\fs20\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f3\fs20\lang1033\i0\b0 1.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Cry aloud, and spare not; lift up thy voice as with a trumpet, and declare to my people their sins, and to the house of Jacob their  iniquities. }2.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  They seek me day by day, and desire to know my ways, as a people that had done righteousness, and had not
 forsaken the  judgment of their God: they now ask of me righteous judgment, and desire to draw nigh to God, }3.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  saying, Why have we fasted, and thou  regardest not? [why] have we afflicted our souls, and thou didst not know it? Nay, in the days of your fas
ts ye find your pleasures, and all  them that are under your power ye wound. }4.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  If ye fast for quarrels and strifes, and smite the lowly with [your] fists, wherefore do ye fast  to me as [ye do] this day, so that your voice may be heard in crying? }5.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  I hav
e not chosen this fast, nor [such] a day for a man to afflict his  soul; neither though thou shouldest bend down thy neck as a ring, and spread under thee sackcloth and ashes, neither thus shall ye call fast  acceptable. }6.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  I have not chosen such a fast, s
aith the Lord; but do thou loose every burden of iniquity, do thou untie the knots of hard  bargains, set the bruised free, and cancel every unjust account. }7.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Break thy bread to the hungry, and lead the unsheltered poor to thy  house: if thou seest one na
ked, clothe [him], and thou shalt not disregard the relations of thine own seed. }8.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Then shall thy light break forth  as the morning, and thy health shall speedily spring forth: and thy righteousness shall go before thee, and the glory of God shall compass
  thee. }9.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Then shalt thou cry, and God shall hearken to thee; while thou art yet speaking he will say, Behold, I am here. If thou remove from  thee the band, and the stretching forth of the hands, and murmuring speech; }10.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  and [if] thou give bread to the 
hungry from thy heart, and  satisfy the afflicted soul; then shall thy light spring up in darkness, and thy darkness [shall be] as noon-day: }11.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  and thy God shall be with  thee continually, and thou shalt be satisfied according as thy soul desires; and thy
 bones shall be made fat, and shall be as a well watered  garden, and as a fountain [from] which the water has failed.   }}
