\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s8\cf0\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af3\afs20\lang1033\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe1033\hich\f3\fs20\lang1033\loch\f3\fs20\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f3\fs20\lang1033\i0\b0 26.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And Joseph entered into the house, and they brought him the gifts which they had in their bands, into the house; and they did him  reverence with their face to the ground. }27.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And he asked them, How are ye? and he said to them, Is your father, the old 
man of whom ye  spoke, well? Does he yet live? }28.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And they said, Thy servant our father is well; he is yet alive. And he said Blessed be that man by God;  and they bowed, and did him reverence. }29.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And Joseph lifted up his eyes, and saw his brother  Benja
min, born of the same mother; and  he said, Is this your younger brother, whom ye spoke of bringing to me? and he said, God have mercy on thee, my son. }30.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And Joseph  was troubled, for his bowels yearned over his brother, and he sought to weep; and he wen
t into  his chamber, and wept there. 31 And he  washed his face and came out, and refrained himself and said, Set on bread. }1.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And Joseph could not refrain himself when all were  standing by him, but said, Dismiss all from me; and no one stood near Joseph,
 when he made himself known to his brethren. }2.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And he  uttered his voice with weeping; and all the Egyptians heard, and it was reported to the house of Pharaoh. }3.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And Joseph said to his  brethren, I am Joseph; doth my father yet live? And his brethren co
uld not answer him, for they were troubled. }4.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And Joseph said to his  brethren, Draw nigh to me; and they drew nigh; and he said, I am your brother Joseph, whom ye sold into Egypt. }5.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Now then be not  grieved and let it not seem hard to you that ye sold m
e hither, for God sent me before you for life. }6.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  For this second year there is famine  on the earth, and there are yet five years remaining, in which there is to be neither ploughing, nor mowing. }7.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  For God sent me before you,  that there might be left to
 you a remnant upon the earth even to nourish a great remnant of you. }8.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Now then ye did not send me hither, but  God; and he hath made me as a father of Pharaoh and lord of all his house, and ruler of all the land of Egypt. }9.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Hasten, therefore, and go  u
p to my father, and say to him, These things saith thy son Joseph: God has made me lord of all the land of Egypt; come down therefore to  me, and tarry not. }10.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And thou shalt dwell in the land of Goshen of Arabia; and thou shalt be near me, thou and thy s
ons, and thy sons'  sons, thy sheep and thine oxen, and whatsoever things are thine. 11 And I will nourish thee there: for the famine is yet for five years; lest  thou be consumed, and thy sons, and all thy possessions. }12.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Behold, your eyes see, and the e
yes of my brother Benjamin, that it is my  mouth that speaks to you. }13.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Report, therefore, to my father all my glory in Egypt, and all things that ye have seen, and make haste and  bring down my father hither. }14.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And he fell on his brother Benjamin's nec
k, and wept on him; and Benjamin wept on his neck. }15.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033   And  he kissed all his brethren, and wept on them; and after these things his brethren spoke to him. 16 And the report was carried into the  house of Pharaoh, saying, Joseph's brethren are come; and P
haraoh was glad, and his household.   }}
