\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s8\cf0\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af3\afs20\lang1033\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe1033\hich\f3\fs20\lang1033\loch\f3\fs20\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f3\fs20\lang1033\i0\b0 23.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  He that keeps his mouth and his tongue keeps his soul from trouble. }24.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  A bold and self willed and insolent man is called a pest: and  he that remembers injuries is a transgressor. }25.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Desires kill the sluggard; for his hands do not choose to do anythi
ng. }26.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  An ungodly man  entertains evil desires all the day: but the righteous is unsparingly merciful and compassionate. }27.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  The sacrifices of the ungodly are  abomination to the Lord, for they offer them wickedly. }28.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  A false witness shall perish; but an
 obedient man will speak cautiously. }29.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  An  ungodly man impudently withstands with his face; but the upright man himself understands his ways. }30.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  There is no wisdom, there is no  courage, there is no counsel against the ungodly. }31.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  A horse is prepared f
or the day of battle; but help is of the Lord. }1.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  A fair name is  better than much wealth, and good favor is above silver and gold. }2.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  The rich and the poor meet together; but the Lord made them both.  }3.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  An intelligent man seeing a bad man severely punish
ed is himself instructed, but fools pass by and are punished. }4.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  The fear of the Lord  is the offspring of wisdom, and wealth, and glory, and life. }5.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Thistles and snares are in perverse ways; but he that keeps his soul will  refrain from them. }7.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  The rich
 will rule over the poor, and servants will lend to their own masters. }8.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  He that sows wickedness shall reap  troubles; and shall fully receive the punishment of his deeds. God loves a cheerful and liberal man; but a man shall fully prove the folly of his 
 works. }9.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  He that has pity on the poor shall himself be maintained; for he has given of his own bread to the poor. He that gives liberally  secures victory and honour; but he takes away the life of them that possess them. }10.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Cast out a pestilent person f
rom the council, and  strife shall go out with him; for when he sits in the council he dishonors all. }11.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  The Lord loves holy hearts, and all blameless persons are  acceptable with him: a king rules with his lips. }12.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  But the eyes of the Lord preserve disc
retion; but the transgressor despises wise words.  }13.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  The sluggard makes excuses, and says, There is a lion in the ways, and murderers in the streets. }14.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  The mouth of a transgressor is a  deep pit; and he that is hated of the Lord shall fall into it. Evi
l ways are before a man, and he does not like to turn away from them; but it is  needful to turn aside from a perverse and bad way. }15.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Folly is attached to the heart of a child, but the rod and instruction are then far  from him. }16.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  He that oppresses the
 poor, increases his own substance, yet gives to the rich so as to make it less. }17.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Incline thine ear to  the words of wise men: hear also my word, and apply thine heart, }18.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  that thou mayest know that they are good: and if thou lay them to  heart, they s
hall also gladden thee on thy lips. }19.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  That thy hope may be in the Lord, and he may make thy way known to thee. }20.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And  do thou too repeatedly record them for thyself on the table of thine heart, for counsel and knowledge. }21.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  I therefore teach thee trut
h, and  knowledge good to hear; that thou mayest answer words of truth to them that question thee. }22.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Do no violence to the poor, for he is  needy: neither dishonor the helpless man in the gates. }23.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  For the Lord will plead his cause, and thou shalt deliv
er thy soul in safety. }24.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Be  not companion to a furious man; neither lodge with a passionate man: }25.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  lest thou learn of his ways, and get snares to thy soul. }26.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033   Become not surety from respect of a man's person. }27.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  For if those have not whence to give
 compensation, they will take the bed that is  under thee. }28.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Remove not the old landmarks, which thy fathers placed. }29.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  It is fit that an observant man and one diligent in his business  should attend on kings, and not attend on slothful men. }1.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  If thou 
sit to sup at the table of a prince, consider attentively the things set before  thee: }2.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  and apply thine hand, knowing that it behooves thee to prepare such meats: but if thou art very insatiable, }3.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  desire not his  provisions; for these belong to a false
 life. }4.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  If thou art poor, measure not thyself with a rich man; but refrain thyself in thy wisdom. }5.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  If  thou shouldest fix thine eye upon him, he will disappear; for wings like an eagle's are prepared for him, and he returns to the house of his  master.
 }6.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Sup not with an envious man, neither desire thou his meats: }7.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  so he eats and drinks as if any one should swallow a hair, and do  not bring him in to thyself, nor eat thy morsel with him: }8.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  for he will vomit it up, and spoil thy fair words. }9.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Say not
hing in the ears of a  fool, lest at any time he sneer at thy wise words. }10.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Remove not the ancient landmarks; and enter not upon the possession of the  fatherless: }11.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  for the Lord is their redeemer; he is mighty, and will plead their cause with thee. }12
.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Apply thine heart to instruction, and  prepare thine ears for words of discretion. }13.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Refrain not from chastening a child; for if thou beat him with the rod, he shall not die. }14.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033   For thou shalt beat him with the rod, and shalt deliver his soul from de
ath.   }}
