\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s8\cf0\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af3\afs20\lang1033\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe1033\hich\f3\fs20\lang1033\loch\f3\fs20\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f3\fs20\lang1033\i0\b0 15.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Son, if thy heart be wise, thou shalt also gladden my heart; }16.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  and thy lips shall converse with my lips, if they be right. }17.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Let not  thine heart envy sinners: but be thou in the fear of the Lord all the day. }18.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  For if thou shouldest keep these th
ings, thou shalt have  posterity; and thine hope shall not be removed. }19.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Hear, my son, and be wise, and rightly direct the thoughts of thine heart. }20.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Be not a  wine-bibber, neither continue long at feasts, and purchases of flesh: }21.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  for every drunkard
 and whore monger shall be poor; and every  sluggard shall clothe himself with tatters and ragged garments.  }22.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Hearken, my son, to thy father which begot thee, and despise not thy  mother because she is grown old. }24.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  A righteous father brings up his chi
ldren well; and his soul rejoices over a wise son. }25.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Let thy  father and thy mother rejoice over thee, and let her that bore thee be glad. }26.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  My son, give me thine heart, and let thine eyes observe my  ways. }27.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  For a strange house is a vessel full of h
oles; and a strange well is narrow. }28.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  For such a one shall perish suddenly; and every  transgressor shall be cut off. }29.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Who has woe? who trouble? who has quarrels? and who vexations and disputes? who has bruises  without a cause? whose eyes are livid? }
30.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Are not those of them that stay long at wine? are not those of them that haunt the places where  banquets are? Be not drunk with wine; but converse with just men, and converse with them openly. }31.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  For if thou shouldest set thine eyes  on bowls and cup
s, thou shalt afterwards go more naked than a pestle. }32.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  But at last such a one stretches himself out as one smitten by a  serpent, and venom is diffused through him as a horned serpent. }33.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Whenever thine eyes shall behold a strange woman, then thy mouth
  shall speak perverse things. }34.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And thou shalt lie as in the midst of the sea, and as a pilot in a great storm. }35.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And thou shalt say, They  smote me, and I was not pained; and they mocked me, and I knew it not: when will it be morning, that I may go a
nd seek those with  whom I may go in company? }1.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  My son, envy not bad men, nor desire to be with them. }2.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  For their heart meditates falsehoods, and their  lips speak mischiefs. }3.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  A house is built by wisdom, and is set up by understanding. }4.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  By discretion
 the chambers are filled with all  precious and excellent wealth. }5.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  A wise man is better than a strong man; and a man who has prudence than a large estate.   }}
