ut of all nations  for a gift to the Lord with horses, and chariots, in litters [drawn by] mules with awnings, to the holy city Jerusalem, said the Lord, as  though the children of Israel should bring their sacrifices to me with psalms into the house of th
e Lord. }21.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And I will take of them priests  and Levites, saith the Lord. }22.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  For as the new heaven and the new earth, which I make, remain before me, saith the Lord, so shall your  seed and your name continue. }23.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And it shall come to pass from month to m
onth, and from sabbath to sabbath, [that] all flesh shall come  to worship before me in Jerusalem, saith the Lord. }24.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And they shall go forth, and see the carcasses of the men that have transgressed  against me: for their worm shall not die, and their fir
e shall shall not be quenched, and they shall be an abhorrence to all flesh.   }}
