\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s8\cf0\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af3\afs20\lang1033\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe1033\hich\f3\fs20\lang1033\loch\f3\fs20\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f3\fs20\lang1033\i0\b0 33.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And when Jacob finished commanding his sons, he drew up his feet into the bed and breathed his last and was added to his people. }1.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033   Then Joseph fell on his father's face and wept over him and kissed him. }2.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And Joseph commanded his servants the embalm
ers to embalm  his father. So the embalmers embalmed Israel. }3.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And they fulfilled his forty days, for such are the days required for embalming. And the  Egyptians mourned for him seventy days. }4.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Now when the days of mourning were over, Joseph spoke to th
e princes of Pharaoh, saying,  "If I have found grace in your sight, speak for me in Pharaoh's hearing, saying, }5.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  \'d4My father adjured me, saying, "In the tomb I dug for  myself in the land of Canaan, there you shall bury me." Now therefore let me go up and
 bury my father, and I will return.'" }6.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And  Pharaoh said, "Go up and bury your father, just as he adjured you." }7.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  So Joseph went up to bury his father, and there went up with him  all the servants of Pharaoh and the elders of his house, and all the elde
rs of the land of Egypt, }8.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  and all the household of Joseph and his  brothers and all his father's household and kindred. But they left their sheep and oxen in the land of Goshen. }9.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  There went up also with  him both chariots and horses, and the encampment
 was very great. }10.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Then they came to the threshing floor of Atad beyond the Jordan,  and they mourned for him with a very great and solemn lamentation. And he continued the mourning for his father seven days. }11.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And the  inhabitants of the land of Canaa
n saw the mourning at the threshing floor of Atad, and they said, "This is a great mourning to the  Egyptians. For this reason one called its name the Mourning of Egypt, which is beyond the Jordan. }12.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And so his sons did this for him  and buried him there
. }13.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  For his sons took him up to the land of Canaan and buried him in the double cave, which cave Abraham bought  for possession of a burying place from Ephron the Hittite opposite Mamre. }14.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Then Joseph returned to Egypt, he and his brothers and  those w
ho went up with him to bury his father. }15.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Now when Joseph's brothers saw their father was dead, they said, "Possibly Joseph  may bear a grudge against us and exact vengeance on us for all the evils we did to him." }16.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  So they came to Joseph, saying, "You
r  father adjured us before he died, saying, }17.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  \'d4Thus you shall say to Joseph, "Forgive them their injustice and their sins, because they did  you evil."' Now therefore, forgive the injustice of the servants of your father's God." And Joseph wept while th
ey were speaking to  him. }18.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And coming near him they said, "We here are your servants." }19.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Then Joseph said to them, "Do not fear, for I am God's. }20.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033   You took counsel against me for evil, but God took counsel on my behalf for good, that it might happe
n as today, that many people might  be nourished." }21.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  He also said to them, "Do not fear. I will nourish you and your households." Thus he comforted them and spoke to  their heart. }22.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  So Joseph dwelt in Egypt, he and his brothers, and all the household o
f his father. And Joseph lived one hundred and ten  years. }23.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And he saw Ephraim's children to the third generation, and the sons of Machir, Manasseh's son, were also brought up on  Joseph's lap. }24.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  And Joseph spoke to his brothers, saying, "I am about t
o die, but God will assuredly visit you and will bring you up  from this land to the land God swore to our fathers, Abraham, Isaac and Jacob." }25.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  Then Joseph adjured the sons of Israel, saying, "In  the visitation wherewith God will visit you, you must ca
rry up my bones with you from here." }26.{\*\cs21\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs32\lang1033\loch\f2\fs32\lang1033  So Joseph died being one hundred and  ten years old, and they embalmed him and put him in a coffin in Egypt.   }}
